WEBVTT

00:03.522 --> 00:04.763
Welcome to Gospel and Life.

00:05.524 --> 00:09.509
How can you become the kind of person whose character deepens during hardship?

00:10.230 --> 00:14.635
The Apostle Peter tells us it's a supernatural work of God that reshapes the heart.

00:15.135 --> 00:23.004
Today, Tim Keller shows us how only a reborn, renewed heart can love others well and face suffering with hope, courage, and joy.

00:23.044 --> 00:31.794
First Peter chapter.

00:32.450 --> 00:34.713
1 verses 13 to 21.

00:37.377 --> 00:40.001
And today we're moving on to the next passage.

00:40.021 --> 00:41.503
The next section is printed in your bulletin.

00:41.643 --> 00:42.764
Please read along with me.

00:43.525 --> 00:49.293
It's 1 Peter chapter 1 verse 22 reading over to verse 3 of chapter 2.

00:49.314 --> 00:50.816
So 1 22 to 2 3.

00:51.456 --> 00:58.987
And tonight we're going to start looking for two weeks tonight and next week at the meaning of this passage as well.

01:00.149 --> 01:01.170
Listen to God's word.

01:02.242 --> 01:26.967
Now that you have purified yourselves by obeying the truth so that you have sincere love for your brethren, love one another deeply from the heart, for you have been born again, not of perishable seed, but of imperishable through the living and enduring word of God, for all men are like grass, and all their glory is like the flowers of the field, the grass withers and the flowers fall, but the word of the Lord stands forever.

01:27.448 --> 01:29.810
And this is the word that was preached

01:29.922 --> 01:30.343
to you.

01:30.383 --> 01:45.124
Therefore, rid yourselves of all malice and all deceit, hypocrisy, envy, and slander of every kind, like newborn babies crave pure spiritual milk, so that by it you may grow up in your salvation, now that you have tasted that the Lord is good."

01:46.286 --> 01:47.207
This is God's word.

01:47.247 --> 01:52.115
All men are like grass and all their glories like the flowers of the field.

01:55.960 --> 01:57.202
Many women have said that.

01:57.794 --> 02:05.562
When I first met my wife, she had been claiming, when we were just dating, she had been claiming this great verse where it says, men are a vain hope.

02:05.582 --> 02:07.624
That was in Psalm, whatever.

02:07.684 --> 02:10.266
But where is that?

02:11.327 --> 02:12.368
Men are all a vain hope.

02:13.269 --> 02:14.190
She changed her mind.

02:14.831 --> 02:26.162
But the generic term here is referring to something more penetrating even than that truism.

02:26.754 --> 02:31.582
Everybody needs to be born again because we are all like grass.

02:31.863 --> 02:33.385
We're all fading.

02:33.886 --> 02:36.090
We're all made of perishable seed.

02:36.892 --> 02:47.570
Now, let's remind ourselves, every time we move from one passage to the next passage, if we're really trying to get a grip of a book of the Bible, you've got to always remember the context.

02:47.746 --> 02:50.009
A text without a context is a pretext.

02:50.290 --> 02:51.572
Somebody once said, I don't know who.

02:51.972 --> 02:54.416
So we always have to remember what the context is.

02:54.817 --> 02:58.242
The book of Peter, first Peter, is all about this subject.

02:58.843 --> 03:12.523
That you can face suffering and troubles in life in such a way that it refines you and purifies you and strengthens you instead of crushing you and breaking you and hardening you.

03:13.044 --> 03:17.010
You can, that's the thesis of the book, that's the main point, you can

03:17.250 --> 03:21.976
face suffering in trials and troubles in such a way that it makes you greater rather than lesser.

03:23.337 --> 03:29.725
There's a saying that the same son that hardens clay melts wax.

03:29.745 --> 03:30.146
Why?

03:31.067 --> 03:35.772
Now we've seen this, and it's a good thing to remind ourselves every time we move, because this is really what Peter's all about.

03:36.333 --> 03:39.637
The same son that hardens clay also melts wax.

03:39.917 --> 03:40.498
Why?

03:41.282 --> 03:43.525
You know, everybody knows this.

03:43.585 --> 03:44.726
Everyone has this experience.

03:44.966 --> 03:49.151
Here's two people, and they both go through the same suffering and the same trauma.

03:49.612 --> 03:54.577
And one person gets more compassionate through the trouble, and the other person gets less compassionate.

03:54.918 --> 03:58.722
One person gets more helpful to other people, the other person gets less helpful.

03:59.683 --> 04:07.292
One person gets morose and bitter, and the other person gets kinder and sweeter.

04:08.533 --> 04:09.074
Why?

04:09.378 --> 04:14.443
Well, the person who's getting morose and bitter and cynical will always say, it was the trouble.

04:15.123 --> 04:16.004
The trouble that did it.

04:16.044 --> 04:18.006
That's what made me the way I am now.

04:18.226 --> 04:19.387
It's because of the persecution.

04:19.427 --> 04:20.368
It's because of the abuse.

04:20.388 --> 04:21.930
It's because of what happened to me.

04:22.570 --> 04:28.476
The real problem with that theory is then how do you account for the other person who went through the very same thing?

04:29.557 --> 04:35.623
You see, if you have clay and you have wax and they're under the same sun, what makes the difference?

04:35.723 --> 04:37.685
Why is one getting harder when he's getting softer?

04:37.925 --> 04:39.026
It's not the sun.

04:39.298 --> 04:40.380
The sun is the same.

04:41.121 --> 04:46.108
It's the internal chemical structure of each substance.

04:46.128 --> 04:56.484
It's how the sun is processed that determines whether or not that circumstance is going to make you harder or softer.

04:57.726 --> 04:59.369
And Peter says it's the same thing here.

05:00.090 --> 05:02.834
How you deal with suffering, how do you deal with trouble?

05:03.874 --> 05:06.137
If you process it properly, it makes you greater.

05:06.257 --> 05:09.360
If you process it improperly, it makes you harder and lesser.

05:09.661 --> 05:14.606
And so he's saying, there is a way to process suffering and trouble in such a way that it benefits.

05:15.227 --> 05:20.893
And don't you see how challenging and at the same time, hopeful it is?

05:20.913 --> 05:22.795
I mean, that's good in bad news.

05:22.855 --> 05:26.740
It comforts you and challenges you at once because on the one hand, it says, there's hope.

05:27.321 --> 05:32.146
No matter how bad your life is, you don't have to let it do this or that to you.

05:33.250 --> 05:33.811
That's hope.

05:35.052 --> 05:35.853
You can overcome it.

05:36.134 --> 05:37.235
But on the other hand, it's a challenge.

05:37.275 --> 05:38.136
It says, watch out.

05:38.276 --> 05:42.261
Passivity is so seductive.

05:42.622 --> 05:47.207
How easy it is to say, the reason I am the way it is, the way I am is I can't help it.

05:47.247 --> 05:48.048
It happened to me.

05:48.329 --> 05:49.190
It did it to me.

05:49.230 --> 05:51.252
So on the one hand, it challenges you.

05:51.272 --> 05:52.975
On the other hand, it gives you tremendous hope.

05:53.255 --> 05:56.759
There is a way of processing the suffering.

05:57.240 --> 06:01.145
Now, in verses 1 to 12 of chapter 1, Peter explained that.

06:01.185 --> 06:02.226
He told us about it.

06:02.594 --> 06:04.216
He said, that's the fact.

06:04.276 --> 06:04.797
It's the case.

06:04.817 --> 06:05.458
And we looked at that.

06:06.059 --> 06:15.032
Then in verses 13 to 21, he explained how or what kind of person processes suffering in such a way.

06:15.453 --> 06:18.777
He begins to talk about, all right, what is that internal structure?

06:18.817 --> 06:20.259
What is that internal processing?

06:21.361 --> 06:24.606
And what he does tell us is it's holy people.

06:25.507 --> 06:27.570
It's people characterized by holiness.

06:28.418 --> 06:36.173
that we'll be able to face those troubles and we'll be able to face that suffering and process suffering in such a way that it just ennobles them.

06:37.495 --> 06:43.487
And we were looking at that for four weeks, right in the center of the passage, be holy for I am holy.

06:43.647 --> 06:45.170
And that's what it's all about.

06:45.474 --> 06:48.277
And as a result, we spent four weeks on it.

06:48.557 --> 06:52.561
And this is Peter trying to say, you want to know how you can process suffering in such a way?

06:52.781 --> 06:53.602
You've got to be holy.

06:53.622 --> 06:54.382
You've got to be holy.

06:54.923 --> 06:58.907
And we talked about it for four weeks, and there's really no reason to go back into it.

06:59.287 --> 07:09.677
But now as Peter keeps moving, Peter, like all the biblical writers, is not just spouting theological concepts, and he's not just rambling.

07:09.937 --> 07:11.959
He is a shepherd and a communicator.

07:12.359 --> 07:15.442
And so he now moves on to tell us

07:15.650 --> 07:17.612
how we can become holy.

07:19.454 --> 07:27.984
You see, the first passage we looked at, you can be the kind of person, he says, that process is suffering in such a way that makes you noble.

07:28.545 --> 07:31.789
Then secondly, the kind of person you have to be is a holy person.

07:31.829 --> 07:32.850
That's what you've got to be.

07:33.691 --> 07:34.652
But he doesn't stop there.

07:35.133 --> 07:40.419
And verse 22 and following, he starts to tell us how we can become holy.

07:40.619 --> 07:43.122
You see, as great as it is to talk about holiness,

07:43.682 --> 07:58.843
as breathtaking and as attractive as holiness is, it's also intimidating because as we've been looking at it, surely some of you have felt, well, if that's what it takes to handle life, if that's what it takes, holiness, as you have been describing it, well, I'll never get there.

07:59.143 --> 08:00.045
How can I be holy?

08:00.345 --> 08:06.834
That's what Peter deals with here because the passages we read, you can see what he starts off with

08:07.650 --> 08:12.095
In verse 22 and 23 is a real description of how a person can be holy.

08:12.516 --> 08:15.319
See, he's actually trying to exhort them to live in a holy way.

08:16.360 --> 08:18.562
He's getting to the exhortation in verse one.

08:18.582 --> 08:22.307
He says, therefore, rid yourself of all malice and deceit, hypocrisy, envy, slander.

08:22.367 --> 08:24.069
We're going to get to that, not tonight, not now.

08:24.269 --> 08:24.850
We'll get to it.

08:25.230 --> 08:28.033
But what he's doing is he's exuding them to live in a holy way.

08:28.994 --> 08:35.762
But like a good communicator, in verse 22 and 23 to 25, he explains how you can get into that condition.

08:35.906 --> 08:43.398
And in verse 22, he summarizes what they're regularly supposed to be doing in order to grow into holiness, which we won't look at now, but next week.

08:43.418 --> 08:48.365
Having purified yourself by obeying the truth so you have sincere love for your brethren, love one another deeply.

08:48.806 --> 08:49.808
There's a process in there.

08:49.828 --> 08:50.689
There's a dynamic.

08:50.709 --> 08:51.390
There's a motor.

08:51.450 --> 08:59.623
There's a process that if you and I adhere to it, we'll grow into that holiness that he's been talking about.

09:00.023 --> 09:01.746
But what I want to talk about tonight

09:02.626 --> 09:13.123
is the basis even for the process, which is seen in verse 23 for, you know, because, see, how can you grow in holiness?

09:13.163 --> 09:17.650
How can you purify yourself by obeying the truth so you have sincere love for your brethren and so on?

09:17.670 --> 09:18.711
How can you grow into holiness?

09:19.012 --> 09:21.075
Because you've been born again.

09:22.798 --> 09:26.103
Peter is showing us, in a sense, the secret to the whole thing.

09:26.143 --> 09:30.610
Or maybe he should say he's working his way back logically to the first cause.

09:32.386 --> 09:33.628
You're suffering, but you know what?

09:33.709 --> 09:36.995
He says, you don't have to let that suffering crush you.

09:37.596 --> 09:38.037
Well, how?

09:38.959 --> 09:39.821
By being coming holy.

09:39.941 --> 09:40.422
Well, how?

09:40.963 --> 09:43.367
By purifying yourself, by obeying the truth, we'll get to that.

09:43.588 --> 09:44.389
But how?

09:44.870 --> 09:46.574
Because you've been born again.

09:46.614 --> 09:48.197
It's all possible, see?

09:48.497 --> 09:49.880
It all is based on this.

09:50.962 --> 09:54.930
Nothing Peter says will apply to you unless you're born again.

09:56.034 --> 10:06.005
Now, one of the things he says, hopefully, not one of his offers, not one of his invitations, not one of his promises, none of it will apply to you unless you're born again, because it's all based on it.

10:06.025 --> 10:12.893
See, for you have been born again, not of perishable seed, but of imperishable through the living and enduring word of God.

10:13.133 --> 10:24.626
Now, what I want to do tonight, it's kind of brief, but I'm going to try to do it, is show you that in these three little verses, there is a tremendous amount of material

10:25.186 --> 10:26.188
on what the new birth is.

10:27.009 --> 10:31.337
Right in here, and I'm at least gonna mention all six of these points, believe it or not, the other six.

10:31.618 --> 10:32.780
I gotta at least mention them all.

10:33.822 --> 10:37.850
The new birth, being born again, is central to Christianity.

10:38.471 --> 10:39.052
It's central.

10:39.553 --> 10:40.995
Secondly, but it's very close.

10:41.015 --> 10:41.897
It's necessary.

10:42.739 --> 10:48.850
Thirdly, it's definite, it's supernatural, it's complete, and it's coherent.

10:49.058 --> 10:51.882
It's a definite, supernatural, complete, coherent experience.

10:51.902 --> 10:53.244
We'll just run on through.

10:53.605 --> 10:56.469
So you have an overview of what the Bible teaches about the new birth.

10:56.509 --> 10:57.230
It's so critical.

10:57.290 --> 11:00.134
And every so many months, you've got to pull the thing out.

11:00.515 --> 11:00.775
Why?

11:00.936 --> 11:01.777
Because let's start.

11:02.438 --> 11:03.079
It's central.

11:04.481 --> 11:08.166
One of the things that's so interesting about this little passage is it's so brief.

11:08.627 --> 11:16.018
He says, because you've been born again, and he mentions it, and he goes on, the very brevity of this reference proves that

11:16.418 --> 11:19.341
The people that Peter was writing to knew about the new birth.

11:20.963 --> 11:22.265
And the point I'm trying to make is this.

11:23.105 --> 11:38.222
Today, the average person, in fact, the average member of a church in this country, thinks of being born again as an option of the type of Christianity, as a party within Christianity.

11:38.963 --> 11:41.366
And that goes utterly against what the scripture teaches.

11:42.327 --> 11:45.170
New birth is not an option, it is central.

11:45.346 --> 11:52.177
The new birth is not something for some people, it's just a given, it's just essential, it's central and essential to what a Christian is.

11:54.701 --> 12:13.170
I think if people are, when people talk about born-again Christians today, or when people, in fact, I've been hearing it, it's really getting shorter and shorter, people are now talking about the born-again's, or she was a born-again, or we had a couple of born-again's in class last year and that sort of thing.

12:13.410 --> 12:20.518
Now, when people talk about born-again Christians, they almost always are thinking about a party, as I just mentioned.

12:20.538 --> 12:34.173
If they're in a very charitable, they're very charitable people, what they mean is born-again people are emotional types who need drama, they need catharsis, they're the kind of people that need that sort of thing.

12:34.533 --> 12:38.217
That's the nicest, that's the nicest sort of thing.

12:38.878 --> 12:42.802
On the other hand, a lot of people think of the born-again as a group

12:42.978 --> 12:52.651
of Christians, a type of Christian who are narrow and bigoted and are right now trying to grab political power and ram their religion and their values down to everybody's throat.

12:53.492 --> 12:55.474
But in a way, it doesn't make any difference.

12:56.095 --> 13:01.963
In all cases, and I'm sure there's some other ways that people define it, a born-again Christian is a kind of Christian.

13:04.025 --> 13:05.788
A born-again Christian is a party.

13:06.929 --> 13:08.331
Therefore, it's an option.

13:08.892 --> 13:10.674
It's something for certain people.

13:10.978 --> 13:15.404
You know, some folks say it's a good thing if you are that kind.

13:16.004 --> 13:18.508
Other people would say it's a bad thing and nobody should do it.

13:20.090 --> 13:22.473
But everybody seems to agree that it's an option.

13:23.254 --> 13:23.494
No.

13:24.936 --> 13:25.537
Not at all.

13:27.739 --> 13:28.901
How can a person be holy?

13:29.902 --> 13:30.923
You have to be born again.

13:30.963 --> 13:33.206
Having been born again.

13:33.246 --> 13:39.314
In the average Protestant church in this city, in the average Protestant church in this city,

13:39.586 --> 13:41.248
They stay away from the idea of being born again.

13:41.288 --> 13:41.849
What do they say?

13:42.109 --> 13:44.632
They say, well, God forgives us.

13:44.712 --> 13:45.533
That's salvation.

13:45.593 --> 13:46.394
God forgives us.

13:46.434 --> 13:47.495
He's a forgiving God.

13:48.577 --> 13:52.161
If we go to Him and tell Him about our faults, He's forgiving and He's very loving.

13:53.022 --> 13:57.287
So salvation is reduced to a kind of loving acceptance period.

13:58.288 --> 14:03.154
And then we also are told that Jesus Christ not only forgives us, but He's our model.

14:03.298 --> 14:05.800
He shows us how we're supposed to live just and compassionate lives.

14:06.081 --> 14:14.849
And we all, then, if you're a Christian, what it means is you know you're forgiven, you go for forgiveness, and then you try your very best to live according to the example and model of Jesus' life.

14:16.711 --> 14:18.533
And that's the Christianity that's given to you.

14:19.333 --> 14:22.857
And you see, being born again, the born again kind of Christianity is considered narrow.

14:23.878 --> 14:24.578
Let me tell you something.

14:24.839 --> 14:27.922
If that's Christianity, just forgiveness.

14:28.382 --> 14:32.626
And then you're on your own to try your very best to live the way Jesus lived.

14:33.058 --> 14:35.943
If that's Christianity, there's no hope.

14:36.664 --> 14:42.995
If that's Christianity, I'm in despair and I would like to say that almost any thinking person should be in despair too.

14:43.837 --> 14:47.803
Christianity is reduced to a kind of general pardon and then you're on your own.

14:47.863 --> 14:50.348
Try your best to live according to Jesus.

14:50.628 --> 14:56.338
When I see Jesus forgiving people, when I see Jesus loving people who persecute him,

14:56.706 --> 15:10.245
When I see people healing, when Jesus is healing people, when I see him serving people, when I see him pouring his life out for people, when I see his utter integrity and his honesty, when I see his self-denial, when I see his humility, does that inspire you?

15:10.285 --> 15:12.649
I don't think it should if you don't believe in the new birth.

15:13.910 --> 15:16.194
He condemns you with every word out of his mouth.

15:16.254 --> 15:17.656
He condemns you with every good deed.

15:17.776 --> 15:18.857
He'll never be like that.

15:19.498 --> 15:20.119
You know that?

15:22.883 --> 15:24.946
He's horribly intimidating.

15:25.698 --> 15:29.723
If you really read him, if you really get to know, most of the people who say, well, that's what Christianity is.

15:29.763 --> 15:33.128
God pardons everybody, and then we try our best to live according to Christ's example.

15:33.549 --> 15:37.754
Anybody who says that in a kind of breezy way, in a kind of hopeful way, has never looked at Christ's example.

15:37.794 --> 15:39.236
They're not really reading about him.

15:39.256 --> 15:40.238
They don't know who he is.

15:43.001 --> 15:48.669
He loved the Lord, his God, with all his heart, soul, strength, and mind, and he loved his neighbor as himself, and there's nobody else that can do that.

15:48.689 --> 15:53.375
In fact, the harder we try to be like Jesus, the farther we see, we fall short.

15:53.415 --> 15:55.538
The more aware we are of our sins,

15:57.570 --> 16:02.203
the new birth promises that God does not just give us pardon.

16:02.383 --> 16:03.406
He gives us new life.

16:03.787 --> 16:04.870
He gives us new power.

16:05.030 --> 16:06.073
He gives us new energy.

16:06.093 --> 16:08.941
You see, He puts His very life in us.

16:11.368 --> 16:12.210
And the Bible

16:12.898 --> 16:23.791
Thankfully, at every point says that the salvation of Jesus Christ is not just a naked pardon, not just a legal thing, not just an abstract thing, but it's an actual thing.

16:23.811 --> 16:25.133
There's power that comes into your life.

16:25.153 --> 16:26.554
You're forgiven and you're born again.

16:26.614 --> 16:27.636
They go together.

16:28.857 --> 16:33.382
You're forgiven up here and you're rejuvenated and renewed and restored in here.

16:33.442 --> 16:36.466
Thank God.

16:37.314 --> 16:39.016
for a complete salvation.

16:39.076 --> 16:43.382
You know, it says, he is able to save to the uttermost those who come to God through him.

16:44.844 --> 16:48.309
Thank God that we have a complete kind of salvation, the new birth.

16:48.810 --> 16:52.294
And every place in the Bible that you read about salvation, you read about the new birth.

16:52.615 --> 17:00.505
In John chapter one, it says, as many as received him, who believed on his name, he gave power and authority to become children of God.

17:00.545 --> 17:02.468
And then it says, who were born?

17:02.508 --> 17:06.994
Not of blood, nor of the will of man, but of God.

17:08.450 --> 17:13.797
What does it mean to be Christian, to receive Jesus Christ, to become children of God, to be born again?

17:14.017 --> 17:15.439
All the same thing, don't you see?

17:16.420 --> 17:17.482
Let me just run through it.

17:17.502 --> 17:20.846
I mean, the evidence is so compelling.

17:20.866 --> 17:30.098
You go to John chapter three, Nicodemus says, you know, teacher, you've got a lot of great teaching, and I don't quite understand you, and Jesus says you must be born again.

17:31.554 --> 17:37.165
John chapter 4, if you look carefully, even when the word's not used, and John chapter 4, he talks to the woman at the well.

17:37.185 --> 17:37.887
And what does he say to her?

17:37.907 --> 17:41.093
He says, whoever drinks the water I give will never thirst again.

17:41.133 --> 17:48.808
But the water I shall give shall be in him as a well of water, springing up into eternal life.

17:49.069 --> 17:51.133
You know, he doesn't use the word, but it's the same thing.

17:51.654 --> 17:53.618
He doesn't just say, I'm going to give you forgiveness.

17:53.794 --> 17:54.955
I'm just going to give you pardon.

17:54.975 --> 17:56.477
I'm going to kind of accept you in a general way.

17:56.818 --> 17:59.340
He says, I'm going to give you something that will come into you.

17:59.561 --> 18:00.282
It's eternal life.

18:00.322 --> 18:04.486
It's the water that I give you that will never, ever, you will never thirst again.

18:04.767 --> 18:07.110
And when it comes into you, it will turn you into a well.

18:07.650 --> 18:08.711
It will spring up in you.

18:08.751 --> 18:10.614
You see, new life will come into you.

18:11.675 --> 18:12.836
You can go to John chapter 10.

18:12.936 --> 18:15.740
He says, I am come that they might have life and have it more abundantly.

18:15.840 --> 18:21.266
Or you can go over to 1 Corinthians where Paul says, if anyone is in Christ, the oldest passed away,

18:22.594 --> 18:23.615
Behold, the new is come.

18:26.038 --> 18:29.783
In Christ Paul says, we are a new creation, a new creature.

18:30.224 --> 18:30.924
Let me just go on.

18:31.225 --> 18:39.015
James chapter 1 verse 18, he chose to give us birth through the word of truth that we might be the first fruits of his creation.

18:39.395 --> 18:48.246
Or second Peter 1, 4, through his great and precious promises, we participate in the divine nature and so escape the corruption that's in the world.

18:49.167 --> 18:51.250
Peter, James.

18:51.970 --> 18:56.215
John, Paul, Jesus, everybody talks about it.

18:57.477 --> 18:58.338
And here's what it means.

18:58.738 --> 18:59.439
Here's what it means.

19:00.421 --> 19:12.195
Anybody that tries to sell you a kind of Christianity without the new birth as the cinecuanon, without the new birth as central, without the new birth as essential, is trying to pass you counterfeit money.

19:14.138 --> 19:14.738
Don't take it.

19:15.820 --> 19:20.786
Any church where it's not preached, any church where the people don't testify that it's happened to them,

19:21.410 --> 19:27.218
any place where people want to back away from it and say, oh, that kind of thing.

19:27.879 --> 19:29.161
That's for a certain kind of person.

19:29.421 --> 19:30.883
What do you mean for a certain kind of person?

19:31.064 --> 19:32.245
Yes, it's for a certain kind of person.

19:32.265 --> 19:38.654
The Bible says it's for all the persons who have received Jesus Christ, who believe in Him, who have become children of Him.

19:39.676 --> 19:40.377
The same thing.

19:41.659 --> 19:44.102
And therefore, it's absolutely central.

19:44.783 --> 19:45.744
And let's go secondly.

19:46.385 --> 19:47.266
The new birth is central.

19:47.407 --> 19:48.648
It's essential to being a Christian.

19:48.849 --> 19:49.810
There's not such thing.

19:50.082 --> 19:51.344
As a Christian, he's not born again.

19:51.865 --> 19:52.886
This is the astute of me.

19:54.048 --> 20:00.037
To say you're born again Christian is an exercise in redundancy, okay?

20:01.319 --> 20:01.940
Just same thing.

20:04.204 --> 20:07.108
Why is there so much pain and suffering in the world?

20:07.569 --> 20:13.618
And how do we handle it in a way that won't destroy us, but could actually make us stronger, wiser, and more hopeful?

20:14.050 --> 20:23.605
All month long on Gospel and Life, Tim Keller is teaching from the book of 1 Peter, and looking at how Peter encouraged early believers who were facing intense suffering in pain.

20:24.346 --> 20:34.903
In his book Walking with God Through Pain and Suffering, Dr. Keller takes a deeper look at how, with God's help, we can face life's most intense challenges and confront the hard questions on suffering.

20:35.444 --> 20:42.034
Through deep pastoral insight and real life stories, Dr. Keller explores how we can face pain and suffering in our own lives.

20:42.082 --> 20:51.679
This month, walking with God through pain and suffering is our thank you for your gift to help gospel and life share the message of Christ's love and compassion with people all over the world.

20:52.220 --> 20:55.666
So request your copy today at gospelandlife.com.

20:55.706 --> 20:58.130
That's gospelandlife.com.

20:58.451 --> 21:01.817
Now here's Dr. Keller with the remainder of today's teaching.

21:04.882 --> 21:07.186
Now secondly, and these are very closely tied,

21:07.458 --> 21:10.162
we see it so central because it's necessary.

21:10.202 --> 21:11.824
Well, it's almost the same thing, not quite.

21:12.164 --> 21:17.411
You see, as we read before, all men are like grass, and all their glories is the flower of the field.

21:17.932 --> 21:22.679
The grass withers and the flowers fall, but the word of the Lord stands forever.

21:22.739 --> 21:23.740
Now, what's it saying?

21:24.861 --> 21:28.066
The reason it's central is because all of us are grass.

21:28.687 --> 21:29.327
Put it this way.

21:30.609 --> 21:34.194
I'm sure that Jesus Christ talked to many people about the new birth.

21:34.402 --> 21:42.260
But the only person that John, the gospel writer, records talking to Jesus about the new birth is Nicodemus.

21:43.162 --> 21:43.503
Why?

21:44.024 --> 21:46.690
Now I think John had a reason, and here's my guess why.

21:46.730 --> 21:50.098
Nicodemus had it all, had it all together.

21:50.658 --> 22:00.610
First of all, Nicodemus was a Pharisee, and a Pharisee is someone who knew the Bible inside out and was morally scrupulous and a very, very, very conscientious person.

22:01.030 --> 22:05.736
Oh, somebody says yes, but the Pharisees were narrow-minded and bigoted, and Jesus didn't like them.

22:05.756 --> 22:07.237
Of course, that's true, but not this one.

22:08.579 --> 22:12.243
Here's a guy who knew Jesus, who loved Jesus, who was concerned, was open to him.

22:12.844 --> 22:18.130
Here's a man who had risked his entire reputation and his job to talk with him.

22:18.850 --> 22:30.971
So you see, combined with his biblical knowledge and with his moral stipulosity, you have an openness and a flexibility of spirit and a willingness to listen to Jesus.

22:31.412 --> 22:34.157
And of course, he was also a civic leader because he's a member of Sanhedrin.

22:34.317 --> 22:34.858
He had it all.

22:35.039 --> 22:36.581
And what does Jesus say to Nicodemus?

22:36.902 --> 22:37.743
See, this is what's so good.

22:38.204 --> 22:41.490
He says, Nicodemus, you, Nicodemus, you.

22:42.306 --> 22:43.787
You master Bible student.

22:44.048 --> 22:45.729
You morally scrupulous person.

22:46.250 --> 22:47.151
You civic leader.

22:47.331 --> 22:49.072
You compassionate and open person.

22:49.413 --> 22:51.215
You, fan of Jesus Christ.

22:51.235 --> 23:00.604
You need to be born again, which means none of these things counts for anything with regard to getting into the kingdom of God.

23:00.924 --> 23:02.485
You want to get into the kingdom of God, Nicodemus?

23:02.505 --> 23:03.967
These things count zero.

23:04.207 --> 23:09.152
You're in the very same spot as Mary Magdalene, the street prostitute.

23:10.393 --> 23:11.474
They count zero.

23:11.778 --> 23:13.500
Well, somebody says, how can that be?

23:13.540 --> 23:14.701
How could that be?

23:14.721 --> 23:16.443
In fact, that's what Nicodemus said.

23:16.804 --> 23:17.484
How can that be?

23:17.885 --> 23:19.066
Why do I need to be born again?

23:19.366 --> 23:21.569
Maybe this person or that person, why do I need to be born again?

23:22.109 --> 23:23.451
And Jesus says, marvel not.

23:23.531 --> 23:24.452
Are you a teacher in Israel?

23:24.472 --> 23:25.153
You don't know these things.

23:25.473 --> 23:30.659
Look, a person at sea level looks at a person standing on a 100-foot hill and fills that person's up pretty high.

23:30.859 --> 23:35.164
And the person on the 100-foot hill looks down at the person on sea level and thinks that person is down pretty low.

23:35.384 --> 23:40.850
But the person on the top of Mount Everest, 29, 30,000 feet high,

23:41.314 --> 23:45.579
Looking down on these two people know that they are virtually the same distance from the summit.

23:46.060 --> 23:48.062
I mean, the distance is virtually nil.

23:48.723 --> 23:53.970
And anybody who thinks the person on the 100-foot hill is way high up, has the limited perspective.

23:54.811 --> 23:56.393
You know, it has a limited horizon.

23:57.354 --> 24:01.559
In the same way, God looks down at us and we're all ravaged with sin.

24:01.619 --> 24:02.380
What is sin?

24:03.201 --> 24:07.026
Well, sin, the Bible tells us, is playing God.

24:08.367 --> 24:08.968
You know what that means?

24:09.228 --> 24:10.610
It means you're your own Savior.

24:11.106 --> 24:14.049
It means you're your own judge and you're living for your own glory.

24:14.709 --> 24:15.830
You're your own savior.

24:15.870 --> 24:18.813
That means you think you know how you can become an acceptable person.

24:18.853 --> 24:20.895
You've found ways to earn your salvation, see?

24:21.175 --> 24:22.937
You define your salvation, you get there.

24:22.957 --> 24:23.718
You're your own judge.

24:23.958 --> 24:26.060
You call the shots, what is right and wrong in your life?

24:26.520 --> 24:28.522
You live for your own glory, hmm?

24:28.542 --> 24:29.443
For your own happiness.

24:30.224 --> 24:30.724
What are you doing?

24:30.744 --> 24:31.545
You're your own God.

24:31.565 --> 24:40.914
Now I know the last 80 years almost, you know, all your professors and all of our colleges and universities have said that's a mature, modern 20th century individual.

24:41.442 --> 24:43.205
but the Bible says it's the essence of sin.

24:44.507 --> 24:55.062
Because what you're, and the reason your life is going so poorly is because you have taken on a job that you're unqualified for, and all of us know what it's like to be in a job you're under qualified, you're under qualified for, you can't handle.

24:56.384 --> 25:00.310
Now, here's Nicodemus and here's Mary Magdalene, and they're both doing the same thing.

25:00.330 --> 25:01.672
They're just spinning out.

25:03.295 --> 25:04.817
They're living to be their own God.

25:04.837 --> 25:06.299
They're living to be their own Savior.

25:06.319 --> 25:07.521
They're living to be their own Judge.

25:07.641 --> 25:10.706
They're just spinning out this in a different way.

25:11.650 --> 25:17.816
You know, you can walk into a hospital ward and here's a woman and she's raving and she's screaming and she says she's in pain.

25:18.116 --> 25:19.417
And here's another person over here.

25:21.359 --> 25:23.801
Calmly asleep with a smile on her face.

25:24.482 --> 25:25.343
Which one's more sick?

25:26.664 --> 25:27.645
Don't judge too quickly.

25:27.965 --> 25:34.091
Maybe this person has just got a raving fever and it's about to break and maybe this person is dying of a tumor on the inside and doesn't have long to live.

25:35.132 --> 25:35.672
Don't you see?

25:36.033 --> 25:37.014
Which one's more of a sinner?

25:37.514 --> 25:39.356
Mary Magdalene, huh?

25:39.376 --> 25:41.618
With a raving fever or Nicodemus?

25:42.146 --> 25:47.313
with the silent self-righteousness, eating away at his entrails spiritually.

25:48.335 --> 25:55.285
Oh, the Bible's penetration sweeps away all of the worldly superficial distinctions between good and bad.

25:55.345 --> 25:57.568
It doesn't talk about good and bad the same way we do.

25:57.849 --> 26:00.572
A hundred feet down, you know, up and down on sea level.

26:01.193 --> 26:03.477
From God's point of view, there is no difference.

26:04.057 --> 26:04.839
All are grass.

26:05.379 --> 26:06.100
All are fading.

26:06.661 --> 26:07.282
None.

26:07.842 --> 26:09.063
are righteous, no not one.

26:09.484 --> 26:17.413
Every one of us, some in morally respectable ways, some are using morality and using religion and using the church as a way to be their own Savior.

26:17.613 --> 26:22.598
And other people are killing and murdering and raping as a way of being their own Savior.

26:23.199 --> 26:34.111
And God looks at them and says, all our grass, Nicodemus, all of your accomplishments, all of your abilities, they count zero.

26:35.653 --> 26:36.914
You must be born again.

26:37.922 --> 26:38.783
Now that's good news.

26:39.664 --> 26:43.748
That's the reason why the new birth is central, because it's necessary for everybody, no matter who you are.

26:43.768 --> 26:44.890
By the way, that's good news, isn't it?

26:45.490 --> 26:48.533
If any of you have been in New York for a while, you know it's good news.

26:49.535 --> 26:49.995
You know why?

26:50.415 --> 27:00.346
Because if you live in New York, you know there's a lot of people who for years and years have said to you, you know, explore your desires, try things out, don't limit your options.

27:00.867 --> 27:02.448
And so you've experimented with a lot of things.

27:02.889 --> 27:03.990
Yes, you've experimented.

27:04.030 --> 27:07.634
And you've tried a lot of things.

27:09.154 --> 27:16.023
You know, some of your concoctions have eaten their way right through your test tube and down into your knee, right through your clothes.

27:16.583 --> 27:19.647
You've really made a mess of things with all of your experimenting.

27:20.068 --> 27:25.014
And you've done some things that you can't forget, and you've done some things that make you feel awful and dirty.

27:27.897 --> 27:28.758
Here's the good news.

27:29.720 --> 27:31.602
You're not behind.

27:32.386 --> 27:36.332
You look at these other people who seem to have got it together morally.

27:36.352 --> 27:39.416
They seem to have got it together vocationally and look at yourself and look where you are.

27:40.158 --> 27:40.859
This is the good news.

27:41.099 --> 27:43.943
You, Nicodemus, you, Mary Magdalene, you're in the same spot.

27:44.444 --> 27:46.908
Don't you see, friends, no matter what you've done with your life, you're not behind.

27:46.988 --> 27:48.310
You're not behind the Nicodemuses.

27:49.672 --> 27:50.593
You must be born again.

27:50.653 --> 27:52.676
That's good news.

27:54.439 --> 27:55.160
And it's bad news.

27:56.121 --> 27:56.582
Don't you see?

27:56.942 --> 27:59.346
It's hope and it's challenge.

28:00.034 --> 28:01.575
You must be born again white.

28:02.136 --> 28:02.837
All are grass.

28:03.517 --> 28:04.258
All are grass.

28:04.779 --> 28:06.840
Thirdly, we said the new birth is central.

28:06.901 --> 28:10.044
Secondly, we said the new birth is necessary.

28:10.084 --> 28:13.006
But now we can actually move more quickly and just say, what is it?

28:13.487 --> 28:18.311
It is a definite supernatural, complete, and coherent event.

28:18.331 --> 28:23.116
First of all, when it says you have been born again, that is in the Greek.

28:23.376 --> 28:25.678
It's a past perfect.

28:25.818 --> 28:29.522
Now, a past perfect means an event that happened

28:30.210 --> 28:34.676
and is over, but its effects continue.

28:35.157 --> 28:39.803
A past perfect is an event that's over and is done with, but its effects continue.

28:40.084 --> 28:44.350
So, for example, in English, it's like, you know, in this case it's not much different than our English language.

28:44.570 --> 28:50.919
If you say, I was accepted at Harvard, well, you were accepted at Harvard, that's a past thing that happened.

28:51.419 --> 28:53.362
You were accepted at Harvard two years ago.

28:53.698 --> 28:54.459
And it's over.

28:54.479 --> 28:55.401
The acceptance is over.

28:55.481 --> 29:01.270
But now, of course, the effects, the fact that you have access to the educational resources of the institution, the effects continue.

29:01.310 --> 29:01.751
But it's over.

29:02.252 --> 29:08.902
When the Bible says you must be born again, when it says you have been born again, it's talking about a definite action in the past.

29:10.705 --> 29:11.867
You know what it means to be a Christian?

29:12.688 --> 29:17.255
A Christian is not somebody who's sort of endlessly hoping to, trying to be a good person.

29:18.197 --> 29:18.898
Oh, no.

29:19.170 --> 29:20.511
Something has happened to you.

29:20.732 --> 29:21.913
There is a definite event.

29:21.953 --> 29:23.594
There is a definite moment.

29:24.695 --> 29:27.818
Now, having said that, be careful.

29:28.359 --> 29:29.520
People just live it.

29:29.540 --> 29:30.781
Let me just give you an illustration here.

29:30.801 --> 29:40.230
People feel that in order to ensure they're born again or in order to be sure somebody else is born again, that you've got to be conscious of when that moment was.

29:40.410 --> 29:40.871
Not always.

29:40.971 --> 29:41.271
Oh, no.

29:41.792 --> 29:42.853
Think of real births.

29:43.934 --> 29:44.775
Ah, the varieties.

29:45.455 --> 29:48.338
Some babies take forever to come.

29:49.250 --> 29:52.454
Endless contractions, right, mothers, endless contractions.

29:52.555 --> 29:55.499
Three days, you go to the doctor, only two centimeters dilated.

29:55.579 --> 29:56.981
How can I be two centimeters dilated?

29:57.461 --> 29:58.743
On and on and on and on and on it goes.

29:59.023 --> 30:04.211
And some babies, two contractions and wham in the taxi cab, right there on the back seat, in the elevator.

30:05.652 --> 30:08.076
Some babies come forever, takes forever.

30:08.857 --> 30:11.120
An enormous number of contractions, others just come like that.

30:11.160 --> 30:12.041
I felt a little bit of pressure.

30:12.081 --> 30:13.003
Good night, what happened?

30:15.506 --> 30:18.450
Some births are full of pain, other births just a little bit of pressure.

30:19.170 --> 30:30.290
Some babies come out, you know, kicking and screaming and fit and other babies come out almost dead and they rush them into the intensive care unit and maybe days before they even become conscious.

30:31.532 --> 30:34.257
Are any of these babies more born than any other ones?

30:35.259 --> 30:37.984
Do we talk about, oh, that one wasn't born as much as that one was?

30:38.064 --> 30:38.284
No.

30:38.765 --> 30:39.587
We don't talk about that.

30:39.607 --> 30:43.794
They were all born because there was a moment in which they passed from death to life.

30:44.706 --> 30:48.031
the moment from which they passed actually in their case from darkness into light.

30:48.311 --> 30:51.235
And in the same way, what does it mean to be born again spiritually?

30:51.996 --> 30:56.943
It means that though there may be incredible varieties of ways in which people come.

30:58.185 --> 31:01.089
Each one of us is born again as the next.

31:01.930 --> 31:04.634
There's a moment, but you may not be conscious of where that moment is.

31:06.757 --> 31:09.521
You know, C. Everett Coop tells the story of his conversion.

31:10.022 --> 31:13.106
He was a surgeon at Children's Hospital in Philadelphia, and one night,

31:13.250 --> 31:21.242
a nurse, a lady that he knew, took him to 10th Presbyterian Church, and he sat in the balcony, and he listened to the sermon, and he thought, this is interesting.

31:21.522 --> 31:23.345
And he says, I was an observer.

31:23.405 --> 31:24.186
I thought it was interesting.

31:24.227 --> 31:24.948
I thought I'd come back.

31:24.988 --> 31:25.649
I didn't really get it.

31:25.669 --> 31:26.250
I didn't really know.

31:26.610 --> 31:29.014
He says, one year later, he had not missed a service.

31:30.135 --> 31:33.320
And he says, I suddenly realized about a year later that I wasn't an observer anymore.

31:33.340 --> 31:34.161
I was a participant.

31:34.662 --> 31:35.644
I wasn't a seeker anymore.

31:35.664 --> 31:36.385
I was a worshipper.

31:37.026 --> 31:40.631
He says, I suddenly realized that the same things that were being taught, I believed.

31:40.791 --> 31:42.514
He says, I wasn't sure where it happened.

31:42.818 --> 31:45.321
I realized I was born again, but I'm not sure where, you see?

31:46.042 --> 32:03.184
On the other hand, you have Martin Luther, he's sitting there and he doesn't understand, he doesn't understand, he's reading Romans 1, 17 and he says, suddenly I realized that there's a righteousness that comes from God and is received by faith and the moment I receive it, I begin to live and he says at that moment, I felt I was ushered through open gates into paradise, you see?

32:03.684 --> 32:08.270
Some people, all the contractions of the world, they take forever, some people, two contractions and in the back of the taxi cab.

32:10.152 --> 32:11.474
But they're all born again.

32:11.906 --> 32:13.047
There's a definite event.

32:13.508 --> 32:16.351
There's a definite moment in which it happens.

32:16.971 --> 32:18.453
So it's definite, okay?

32:18.933 --> 32:19.794
Be very careful, though.

32:20.355 --> 32:20.755
You know what?

32:21.195 --> 32:28.423
From what I can tell, a mother who's had one child likes to talk to an unexpected mother who's had no children and tell her all about it.

32:28.443 --> 32:29.304
Oh, this is how it'll be.

32:30.084 --> 32:34.109
You know, once you've had eight or nine children, you stop giving advice, they say.

32:34.169 --> 32:39.474
Not just because you're tired, because you realize there is no way that they all come.

32:40.034 --> 32:42.077
They all come differently, except they all come.

32:42.117 --> 32:44.401
They're all born, but one is not more born than the next.

32:45.223 --> 32:46.044
It's a definite event.

32:46.345 --> 32:49.710
It's something happens to you, but secondly, it's a supernatural event.

32:50.792 --> 32:55.620
Because it says, you're born of imperishable seed, not of perishable.

32:56.301 --> 32:59.346
Now what that means is something fairly simple, but extremely important.

33:00.669 --> 33:03.954
The Greek word for born again here is a little unusual.

33:04.290 --> 33:09.740
The normal word for born is geneo, from which we get our word generation, you know, to generate something.

33:09.901 --> 33:11.243
You know, that makes sense.

33:11.263 --> 33:19.740
But this word is on a geneo, which actually is the word not for the mother's role in birth, but the father's role insemination.

33:20.180 --> 33:23.026
It's actually a word for planting a seed.

33:23.367 --> 33:25.170
And it tells us about that seed.

33:25.570 --> 33:31.298
It says we've been born again, not of perishable seed, but of imperishable through the living and enduring word of God.

33:31.318 --> 33:33.241
Now it doesn't say that the word of God is the seed.

33:33.621 --> 33:35.484
It says it comes, and I'll mention that in one second.

33:36.265 --> 33:37.627
But what is that imperishable seed?

33:37.968 --> 33:39.590
You're built of perishable seed.

33:40.091 --> 33:45.298
This is the reason why the older I get, the more I start to fall apart.

33:45.698 --> 33:47.781
I'm made of perishable seed.

33:48.261 --> 33:53.488
This is the reason why you and I find no matter how hard we try, we say, I'm going to be a new person.

33:54.148 --> 33:55.510
You know, you have New Year's resolutions.

33:55.750 --> 33:57.472
I'm turning over a new leaf and you never can do it.

33:57.673 --> 33:58.674
You're made of perishable.

33:59.575 --> 34:04.221
But this tells us that the imperishable seed can be planted.

34:04.261 --> 34:05.102
And what is that seed?

34:05.222 --> 34:06.323
It's 2 Peter 1, 4.

34:06.884 --> 34:09.007
We become partakers of the divine nature.

34:09.708 --> 34:10.869
It's laid into us.

34:11.309 --> 34:12.331
It's put into us.

34:13.632 --> 34:14.994
It's pressed into us.

34:15.554 --> 34:17.156
And that is what you need.

34:18.298 --> 34:19.319
And that's what comes.

34:20.501 --> 34:21.522
It's supernatural.

34:21.882 --> 34:22.704
Ah, but not only.

34:22.744 --> 34:24.586
Okay, it's a definite event.

34:24.606 --> 34:26.008
It's a supernatural event.

34:26.148 --> 34:27.790
It comes from imperishable seed.

34:28.211 --> 34:28.531
Okay?

34:28.992 --> 34:31.395
But then look, it's a complete change.

34:31.676 --> 34:34.840
The word born again, why would Peter talk about it this way?

34:35.240 --> 34:36.222
Why would he talk about it?

34:36.662 --> 34:37.904
Why did Jesus use the term?

34:37.944 --> 34:38.985
Why did they all use the term?

34:39.286 --> 34:40.307
Because it's so radical.

34:40.968 --> 34:45.554
They wouldn't talk about being born again unless they were trying to say this is as radical a change as possible.

34:46.274 --> 34:48.957
And somebody says, all right, well, tell me what exactly this means.

34:49.498 --> 34:51.641
When I get this imperishable seed, what happens?

34:51.941 --> 34:53.343
You get a totally new outlook.

34:54.764 --> 34:58.869
You become totally new because you see things differently and you desire things differently.

34:58.890 --> 35:01.072
And I don't have really any time to go too much into this.

35:01.493 --> 35:03.575
But just consider this.

35:05.237 --> 35:08.381
A plant is a lower order of life than an animal.

35:09.483 --> 35:12.266
And human beings are higher orders of life than an animal.

35:12.286 --> 35:13.888
And animals lower order of life than a human being.

35:13.948 --> 35:14.208
Why?

35:14.769 --> 35:15.570
The plant

35:15.746 --> 35:16.687
has sensation.

35:17.508 --> 35:18.630
It can sense some things.

35:19.511 --> 35:23.536
But there's a lot of things that it can't sense in its environment because it can't see.

35:24.597 --> 35:25.438
The animal can see it.

35:25.859 --> 35:26.700
All right, but let's move up.

35:27.161 --> 35:36.853
The animal can see a lot of things that the plant can't see, but it can't see a lot of things that the human beings can see because it doesn't have rational sight.

35:36.873 --> 35:42.981
For example, it can't tell the difference between tragedy and cruelty and justice and compassion.

35:43.261 --> 35:43.922
We see it.

35:44.226 --> 35:45.447
Is there such a thing as cruelty?

35:45.467 --> 35:46.749
Yes, but an animal can't see it.

35:47.529 --> 35:50.392
And so you see, in a sense, there are different orders of life.

35:51.213 --> 35:57.200
And to the next lower order of life, the next higher order of life is incomprehensible.

35:57.520 --> 36:02.445
And to the higher order of life, the next lower order of life is a form of living death.

36:03.786 --> 36:09.392
If a person becomes a vegetable, we call them, they're still alive, but they've gone down.

36:09.432 --> 36:11.154
Now, the Bible tells us

36:11.490 --> 36:17.960
that when the imperishable seed comes into your life, you are brought to the highest order of life of all, eternal life.

36:18.341 --> 36:19.062
Oh, what does that mean?

36:19.983 --> 36:26.053
What it means is, as Jesus says to Nicodemus, you must see the kingdom of God.

36:27.115 --> 36:28.617
You have to be born again to see it.

36:29.278 --> 36:32.323
He didn't just say to enter it, though he said that, to see it, you won't get it.

36:33.284 --> 36:34.246
You won't understand it.

36:35.528 --> 36:39.314
Before you're born again, you may believe in a general way

36:39.618 --> 36:40.499
that God is holy.

36:40.639 --> 36:44.765
You may believe in a general way that Jesus died for you, but when you're born again, here it is, here it is.

36:45.185 --> 36:45.946
You see it.

36:47.688 --> 36:48.590
It becomes real.

36:49.311 --> 36:50.192
Heaven, hell.

36:50.792 --> 36:51.914
Jesus dying on the cross.

36:52.194 --> 37:00.205
All these things, before you're born again, you may either think they're nonsense or you make believe in them in a general way, but you don't see them when you're born again, you see them.

37:00.245 --> 37:00.465
Why?

37:00.785 --> 37:03.969
Because the imperishable seed, imperishable seed comes through the word of God.

37:04.370 --> 37:05.632
It always comes through the truth.

37:06.092 --> 37:07.474
It is a coherent

37:08.706 --> 37:10.108
It's a coherent experience.

37:10.789 --> 37:16.796
Look, when William Holland was one of the Wesley's friends.

37:17.177 --> 37:18.218
You know how you got converted?

37:18.739 --> 37:19.800
This is in the 1740s.

37:20.361 --> 37:25.708
He said, Mr. Charles Wesley was reading the preface to Martin Luther's commentary on the Galatians out loud.

37:26.409 --> 37:28.051
And I heard these words, what?

37:28.151 --> 37:29.253
Have we then nothing to do?

37:29.373 --> 37:36.562
No nothing but only accept of him who of God is made unto us to be wisdom and righteousness and sanctification and redemption.

37:37.282 --> 37:42.727
And when I heard those words, he said, there came such a power over me as I cannot well describe.

37:42.787 --> 37:45.210
My great burden finally fell off at an instant.

37:45.690 --> 37:48.353
My heart was so filled with peace and love that I burst into tears.

37:48.893 --> 37:52.677
My friends, perceiving me so affected, fell on their knees around me and prayed.

37:52.717 --> 37:58.743
And when afterwards I went out into the street, I could scarcely feel the ground I was walking on.

37:58.903 --> 37:59.423
What happened?

38:00.344 --> 38:02.386
He had heard the gospel.

38:03.948 --> 38:06.450
He had heard it before, but he never saw it.

38:06.722 --> 38:11.888
He had heard that Jesus died for him, that he couldn't be saved by his good deeds, but only by the grace of Jesus Christ.

38:11.909 --> 38:12.930
But he finally saw it.

38:13.170 --> 38:15.593
The imperishable seed came in through the Word of God.

38:16.414 --> 38:23.002
I tell you, when people say the new birth is for emotional types, that is the silliest thing in the world.

38:23.043 --> 38:26.186
It doesn't say that the imperishable seed comes in through the emotions.

38:26.247 --> 38:27.508
It comes in through the understanding.

38:27.909 --> 38:28.409
I get it.

38:29.731 --> 38:35.378
And the way you can tell you're born again is, in many cases, the same truths that you may have heard in Sunday school

38:35.490 --> 38:43.579
being raised up in it, or the same truths that make no sense to you after having gone to college and you got rid of all of it, all of a sudden you actually see them.

38:43.599 --> 38:46.983
They become coherent, they become real, they become affecting.

38:47.023 --> 38:48.485
They comfort you now.

38:48.945 --> 38:56.214
You live off them, they thrill you, or they disturb you, but they affect you because you've moved up one more notch.

38:56.915 --> 39:01.900
You're not just a plant, you're not just an animal, you're not just a human being, you're a child of God.

39:02.521 --> 39:03.442
You don't just have

39:03.522 --> 39:08.108
animal life, physical life, you don't just have even rational life, you've got spiritual life.

39:09.730 --> 39:10.612
Has that happened to you?

39:11.973 --> 39:14.897
Look at the baby rolling around on the ground.

39:16.019 --> 39:17.821
She can't tell you too much about herself.

39:17.841 --> 39:21.366
She can't tell you too much about what it means to be born, but you can see she's there.

39:21.406 --> 39:22.307
She's got an appetite.

39:23.409 --> 39:24.390
She can sense things.

39:25.111 --> 39:25.872
Are you born again?

39:25.932 --> 39:30.258
If you're born again, there's life, there's activities, there's vitality.

39:30.626 --> 39:33.730
The truths are dawning on you in ways you never saw before.

39:33.770 --> 39:34.771
Has that ever happened to you?

39:34.911 --> 39:36.173
If not, you're not born again.

39:36.213 --> 39:37.775
Has there been a definite time?

39:38.255 --> 39:42.781
You may not be able to put your finger on the moment, but you can see something happen in this time frame.

39:42.801 --> 39:43.442
Has that happened?

39:44.142 --> 39:45.744
Has something supernatural happened to you?

39:46.045 --> 39:49.769
Have you been changed in such a way that you can't account for those changes?

39:49.990 --> 39:50.991
They must be supernatural.

39:51.011 --> 39:52.493
They can't be naturally explained.

39:53.634 --> 39:56.978
Do you understand this necessity and the centrality of the new birth?

39:57.602 --> 39:59.845
Without it, you can't be holy and without that.

40:00.145 --> 40:05.332
You will never be able to process the suffering and troubles of this life in such a way that it turns you into a great heart.

40:07.254 --> 40:08.396
You must be born again.

40:08.456 --> 40:11.400
Marvel not that I say unto you.

40:11.460 --> 40:13.442
You must be born again.

40:13.482 --> 40:14.123
Let's pray.

40:14.924 --> 40:25.778
Our father, we ask now that you would enable us to rejoice if we are born again and be convicted and aware of it if we are not.

40:26.082 --> 40:48.053
I really ask, Lord, that by your spirit, those who in this room understand the new birth would rejoice in their recognition and their realization of it, and that also those in this room who begin to realize that they have not experienced this, they might be convicted, they might be drawn, they might be attracted, and they might not stop until they find out what it is.

40:48.073 --> 40:50.416
And I pray these things in Jesus' name.

40:51.277 --> 40:51.698
Amen.

40:57.410 --> 40:59.173
Thanks for listening to today's teaching.

40:59.713 --> 41:05.602
It's our prayer that you were encouraged by it and that it helps you apply the gospel to your life and share it with others.

